I posed myself a funny question today: "After five years, what makes you so sure that you don't love her any more"? Interesting question.

I fell in love with a certain kind of woman. This woman was charismatic, funny, intelligent, sexual, loving, the list goes on an on. Over time, however, these things waned. It is one thing for life to change a person to some extent, but their essence never leaves. I watched her metamorphosize, but not into into a being of light. I watched her change into something akin to the bug - human creature in Franz Kafka's "Metamorphosis". The main difference, however is that this monster in the story still cared. In my case, this change was one of an embodiment of hatred. She became her defences and safeguarded what was immediately hers. Her, and her three children. For awhile, I was in those things to be safeguarded. However, I found myself repulsed by her. Our interactions were seething with rage, and her desire to keep me was one no longer marked by love, but of depression, anger, and a fear of losing control.

She was the embodiment of Nihilism as a psychological condition of weakness, because her convictions had all but lost hope, and control was her only means of a will to power, albeit the "will" had long gone. 
I cannot love hatred. I cannot love when someone's self worth is less than that of of a common whore. 
I realised that I no longer loved her the day she truly became ugly to me; the Ides of March indeed.

Not only does #Mercury create and #antigravity effect but, if electrified, it can change completely into 100% pure gold! In March of 1924 In the Tokyo Imperial University, Professor Hantaro Nagaoka electrifies Mercury with about 150,000 volts for four hours and successfully produced a new element, gold. Could he have been the first one to discover this? I am constantly looking up #ancient art and ancient societies like #alchemists and I ALWAYS see the #sign for Mercury in a special place in the artwork. I also notice the #doublehelix all over #AncientArt. If you think about it, electricity is technically produced by individual North and South Pole magnets which are two currents running against one another in a right hand twist which can be drawn exactly like the double helix. Could the double helix be the sign for electricity? Also I believe this was in 2012 when archeologists discovered underground tunnels beneath the #Mayan #Pyramid of the #FeatheredSerpent that contained a bunch of weird artifacts and large pools of Mercury. Could the Mayans have changed Mercury to gold? They did have a crazy amount of gold! What do you think?
